  "text": "The Functional Representation of a CE is defined as a sequence of operations that act on a Calendar Base (CB) -see [CITATION_1] for more details. The Calendar Base is the core calendar reference indicated by a textual unit (such as \"17th century\", \"June 6, 1897\", for instance). Several operators can successively apply upon the CB: (i) Zooming and Shifting Operators (corresponding to textual units such as \"mid\", \"three months before\"), (ii) Zoning Operators (corresponding to textual units such as \"at\", \"before\", \"until\") and (iii) Composition Operators (involved in CEs such as \"from the mid 80s to the mid 90s\"). More precisely, we consider four sets of operators: OpZooming = {ZoomID, ZoomBegin, ZoomEnd, ZoomMiddle} OpShifting = {Shift(u, n); n ∈ Z and u is a unit of time} OpZoning = {ZoningID, Before, After, Until, Since} OpComposition = {Between}",
  "correct_citation": {
